---
By: Dante Alighieri
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 360
    Verse: 5
Tags:
  - Perfection
---
Everything, by an impulse of its own nature, tends toward
perfection. ... Everything is at its best and most perfect when in the
condition intended for it by the First Cause.
